                    <span class="tei-personGrp">
                        <span class="tei-persName"> The monks who accused
                                <span class="tei-persName">Abraham</span> of
                            embezzlement </span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/10510-77" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Sex: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">
                                    Anonymi 3673 </span> were male. <a href="/10510-211" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Occupation(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Anonymi
                                    3673</span> were monks. <a href="/10510-78" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Relationships</h3><p class="indent">Abraham was a monastic authority over Anonymous 3673. <a href="/10510-106" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Abraham was a monastic authority over Anonymous 3673. <a href="/10510-79" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Abraham was a monastic authority over Anonymous 3673. <a href="/10510-85" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Abraham had ecclesiastical authority over Anonymous 3673. <a href="/10510-97" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent">Anonymi
                            3673 of the Convent of John Urtaya disliked Abraham II's
                            appointment of Abraham
                                III as his successor, believing him to be a lowly
                            peasant. Sixty
                                monks left the convent.  <a href="/10510-107" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">The monks
                            serving under Abraham accused him of embezzling monastery funds in
                            order to support his family. Abraham was
                            innocent, but left the monastery to live in the city and lived the rest
                            of his days longing for his former monastic existence.  <a href="/10510-76" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Anonymi 3673
                            of the Convent of John
                                Urtaya urged Bishop Abraham to
                            appoint a new head. Abraham chose Abraham the
                            Shepherd, who was formerly a shepherd from the Village of Thella d
                                Mikhana.  <a href="/10510-98" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
